o engage, point by point, with the specificinterpretive methods of Sunni legal theory. The text thus preserves importantpassages from several Islamic legal theoretical works no longer extant, and inthe process throws light on a critical stage in the development of Islamiclegal theory that would otherwise be lost to history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aIkhtilāf (Islamic law) 0aIkhtilāf (Islamic law). 0aIkhtilāf (Islamic law). 0aIslamic lawxInterpretation and construction. 0aIslamic law-Interpretation and construction. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh1 aCoughlin, John J.1 aSexton, John.1 aStewart, Devin.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107289720 cprintz978147980807640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814790281423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814790281/original  a978-3-11-072897-2  New York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK